1 32-A. Indoor cultivation. "Indoor cultivation" means cultivation of mature cannabis
2 plants that does not meet the definition of "outdoor cultivation" under subsection 41-A.
3 Sec. 7. 28-B MRSA §102-A, sub-§41-A is enacted to read:
4 41-A. Outdoor cultivation. "Outdoor cultivation" means cultivation of mature
5 cannabis plants between the months of March and December in a cultivation area that
6 primarily uses sunlight for such cultivation.'
7 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
8 number to read consecutively.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment amends the
1111 Maine Medical Use of Cannabis Act and the Cannabis Legalization Act by:
12 1. Defining "outdoor cultivation area" under the medical use of cannabis provisions
13 and "outdoor cultivation" and "indoor cultivation" under the adult use cannabis provisions;
14 2. Increasing the number of cannabis plants and expanding the area of canopy of
15 cannabis plants that a medical use caregiver who cultivates mature cannabis plants only in
16 an outdoor cultivation area and who registers based on plant count or canopy may cultivate.
17 The amendment establishes a registration fee for such caregivers; and
18 3. Removing the provision of law under the medical use of cannabis provisions that
19 authorizes an elected official invited by a caregiver for the purpose of providing education
20 to the elected official on cultivation to access a cultivation area and providing instead that
21 any person under the direct supervision of the caregiver may access a cultivation area.
